#necessary libraries
library(data.table)
library(dplyr)
library(psych)
library(ggplot2)
library(MASS)
library(jpeg)
library(smacof)
#labelling the columns of the musk data set 
musk = read.table('musk1.csv', header=FALSE, sep=',')
features <- c("mclass","molecule",sprintf("f%02d", seq(1,166)))
colnames(musk) <- features
# Bartlett's test of sphericity, p.value<0.05 -> H0 rejected. PCA is applicable.
r=cor(musk[,3:168])
cortest.bartlett(r,n=476)
## $chisq
## [1] 226650.7
## 
## $p.value
## [1] 0
## 
## $df
## [1] 13695
#Data standardized is required
scmusk = scale(musk[,-(1:2)])
# MDS - Euclidean distances between rows
distmusk <- as.matrix(dist(scmusk, method = "euclidean"))
mdsmusk <- as.data.frame(cmdscale(distmusk))
mdsmusk$names <- musk[,2]
mdsmusk$names <- as.numeric(mdsmusk$names)
mdsmusk$group <- musk[,1]
mdsmusk$group <- as.numeric(mdsmusk$group)

#to check stress value - good fit in 6 dimensions (but 2 dimensions are selected for plot)
strs = mds(delta = distmusk,ndim = 6, type = "ratio" )

#The graph shows that instances are mostly close and summarizing is appropriate.
xx<- ggplot(mdsmusk, aes(V1, V2, label=names,color=names)) + 
  geom_point(size=3.5) +
  geom_text(check_overlap = TRUE, size=2.5, 
            hjust = "center", vjust = "bottom", nudge_x = 0, nudge_y = 0.4,color="black") + 
  labs(x="", y="", title="MDS by Euclidean") + theme_bw()
xx+scale_color_gradientn(colours = rainbow(5))

#with group shaping 
xxx<- ggplot(mdsmusk, aes(V1, V2, label=names,color=names)) + 
  geom_point(shape=mdsmusk$group, size=3.5) +
  geom_text(check_overlap = TRUE, size=2.5, 
            hjust = "center", vjust = "bottom", nudge_x = 0, nudge_y = 0.4,color="black") + 
  labs(x="", y="", title="MDS by Euclidean") + theme_bw()
xxx+scale_color_gradientn(colours = rainbow(5))

#PCA is applied for scaled dataset - scmusk
pca=princomp(scmusk)
plot(pca)

summary(pca)

#Criterion for component selection -> 2/3 = 0.67. There should be 6 components according to the selection criteria. However, the first two components were used for plotting.

npca=pca$scores
npca=as.data.frame(npca)

plot(npca[,1],npca[,2],main='PCA',xlab='Component-1', ylab='Component-2',col=(npca$grp)+1)

#Summarize instances to bag level inf
baglevel=musk %>%
  group_by(molecule) %>%
  summarise_at(vars(-mclass), funs(mean(., na.rm=TRUE)))
## Warning: funs() is soft deprecated as of dplyr 0.8.0

typeof(baglevel)
## [1] "list"
#Data standardized is required

#quest 2 - read the image and display
library(jpeg)
leo <- readJPEG("F:/boun/hw_2/leo.jpg")
str(leo)
##  num [1:256, 1:256, 1:3] 0.42 0.451 0.443 0.467 0.49 ...

## [1] 256 256   3

#displaying each channel
red<-leo[1:256,1:256,1]
green<-leo[1:256,1:256,2]
blue<-leo[1:256,1:256,3]
par(mfrow=c(1,3))
image(1:256,1:256,t(apply(red,2,rev)))
image(1:256,1:256,t(apply(green,2,rev)))
image(1:256,1:256,t(apply(blue,2,rev)))

#creating noisy
rednoise<-matrix(runif(256*256,0,0.1),256,256)
greennoise<-matrix(runif(256*256,0,0.1),256,256)
bluenoise<-matrix(runif(256*256,0,0.1),256,256)
red=red+rednoise                 
green=green+greennoise                 
blue=blue+bluenoise                 
leo[1:256,1:256,1]=red
leo[1:256,1:256,2]=green
leo[1:256,1:256,3]=blue
img=ifelse(leo>1,1,leo) 
plot(0:256, 0:256, type="n")
rasterImage(img, 0, 0, 256, 256,interpolate=FALSE)

#Transforming noisy image to a grayscale
gry<- leo[,,1]+leo[,,2]+leo[,,3]
gry <- gry/max(gry)
plot(c(0,1),c(0,1),t='n')
rasterImage(gry, 0,0,1,1)
